Deji Elumoye in AbujaÂ President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled with the Arewa Consultative Forum (ACF) over the demise of its National Publicity Secretary, Emmanuel Yawe. The President, according to a release issued on Friday by his Media Adviser, Femi Adesina,commiserated with family members, friends and associates of Yawe, particularly in the media, where he served meritoriously as a reporter and editor of various publications for many years. President Buhari prayed that the Almighty God will receive the soul of the departed and comfort all his loved ones.